cast.overview: Freddie, a volatile, heavy-drinking veteran who suffers from post-traumatic stress disorder, finds some semblance of a family when he stumbles onto the ship of Lancaster Dodd, the charismatic leader of a new "religion" he forms after World War II.
cast.title: The Master

details.biography: Jennifer Neala Page attended Rose Bruford Conservatory of Speech and Drama in London. Her career started in Theatre with credits including; Dancing At Lughnasa, A Midsummer Night's Dream, Newsrevue, Neil Labute's Bash (for which she won a Golden Production Award), and The Really Useful Company/ Andrew Lloyd Webber's Daisy Pulls It Off in London's Westend to rave reviews.
details.name: Jennifer Neala Page
